headline: Freeport-McMoRan (NYSE:FCX) Q1 Earnings Dip and Completes Share Buyback of US$1,974 Million
summary: Freeport-McMoRan (NYSE:FCX) recently reported a 5.61% increase in its share price over the past week, a period marked by its first-quarter earnings release showing declines in sales and net income. headline: Freeport-McMoRan flags higher costs due to tariffs, posts lower quarterly profit
summary: "FCX is monitoring potential indirect impacts of U.S. trade policy on economic growth and the potential for impacts on demand for copper," the company said.  Freeport-McMoRan said it produced 868 million recoverable pounds of copper in the first quarter, lower than the 1.09 billion recoverable pounds it reported a year earlier.
